<p>During the month of February we were contacted by an Educational Foundation in the US. They offered faculty-led travel programs and wanted to plan a trip in Northern Italy for a class of students in the month of July. They asked for help from Solede in order to plan the itinerary in every detail and carry out the tour once in Italy.</p>

<h3></h3>

<h3><strong>LISTEN TO PEOPLE’S NEEDS</strong></h3>

<p>We tried to better understand their needs and requests, and gather all the information we could. Since the class was studying the field of economics and the professors travelling with them taught International management and Marketing, they were interested in visiting some economic companies in the country. This lead us to choose Milan as the main city during the sejour, thanks to the large number of companies and financial-related societies in that area of Italy.<br>Due to the numerous group (40 students) we decided to limit hotel changes and opted to sleep in Milan for 4 nights, in Modena for 3 nights (students wanted to visit Ferrari Museum), and then Milan for the last night.<br>We started working on the project and found some companies willing to host 40 students and show them their headquarters or company museums: a world-famous design company (Kartell) and a leading pharmaceutical company (Zambon). We managed to plan a visit to the historical archives of Intesa San Paolo bank (one of the leading banks of Italy), and also a visit to the most important University of Economy in Milan, Bocconi University, where professors would have been happy to make a presentation of their courses and give an overview of the university. <strong>We always do our best to fulfil our clients&#39; needs and meet their expectations.</strong></p>

